cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper presents a new model of motor structure learning using deep reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to model motor structure learning, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses motor control and adaptation, which are important topics in robotics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents a new model of motor structure learning using AI techniques, which could be relevant to the AI community. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses recurrent neural networks to account for learning-to-learn effects, which could be relevant to the neural computing community. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly discuss computer vision, the use of deep learning techniques could be relevant to the computer vision community.
